org.net4care.skype.api

Class Net4CareSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.net4care.skype.api.Net4CareSession

  • public class Net4CareSession
extends Object
    Session Object. Encapsulates common aspects of the SkypeKit-based Java s. These include:
    • target account name
    • console PrintStream (based off System.out) that specifies autoFlush as true
    • activity indicators, such as the associated Account's login status and whether a call is in progress
    • transport-related members:
      • SkypeKit runtime IP address
      • SkypeKit runtime port number
      • com.skype.ipc.ClientConfiguration instance
    • Skype instance
    • Account instance
    • SignInMgr instance
    • PhysicianListeners instance (s-specific "helper" class instance that implements the various "listener" interfaces)
    • setupAudioDevices(int, int) method to commonize assignment of microphone/speaker devices for calls
    Furthermore custom methods have been added by net4care, these are:
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Andrea Drane (ported/refactored from existing C++ code)

      • doCreateSession

        public boolean doCreateSession(String classTag,
                      String accountName,
                      String pathName,
                      Net4CareListeners listeners)
        Creates most everything needed for a session; the Account instance is populated during sign-in.
        Parameters:
        classTag - The 's class name. If null or the empty string, default it to T_TAG_DFLT.
        accountName - The name of the account to use for this . If null or the empty string, fail by throwing a RuntimeException indicating that fact.
        pathName - Pathname of the certificate file, which should be a PEM file.
        Returns:
        • true: session initialized
        • false: session initialization failed due to:
          • no or empty account name
          • com.skype.api.Skype.Init failed - most likely from an invalid AppKeyPair
          • could not obtain an Account instance
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        com.skype..util.SignInMgr

      • doTearDownSession

        public void doTearDownSession()
        Tears down a session.

        Specifically, this involves:
        1. Un-registering the listeners
        2. Disconnecting the transport
        3. "Closing" our Skype instance, which terminates the SkypeKit runtime
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        PhysicianListeners#unRegisterAllListeners()

      • isLoggedIn

        public boolean isLoggedIn()
        Determines if an Account is signed in.

        Specifically, this involves examining the last cached value for the associated Account's status property. Essentially, only a current status of Account.Status.LOGGED_IN returns true

        Caching the status avoids having to query the DB. For mobile devices, WiFi-connected laptops running on battery power, and so forth this typically avoids expending battery charge to transmit the server request.
        Returns:
        • true: currently signed in
        • false: currently signed out or target Account is null
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        com.skype..util.SignInMgr#isLoggedIn(Account)

      • setupAudioDevices

        public boolean setupAudioDevices(int micIdx,
                        int spkrIdx)
        Assigns active input and output devices from among those available. Notifies user regarding the name of the selected devices or whether the request failed. Both devices must exist for the request to succeed.
        Parameters:
        micIdx - Index into the array of available recording devices of the requested input device.
        spkrIdx - Index into the array of available playback devices of the requested output device.
        Returns:
        • true: success
        • false: failure
        Since:
        2.0
        See Also:
        Skype.getAvailableRecordingDevices(), Skype.getAvailableOutputDevices()

      • doAcceptCalls

        public void doAcceptCalls()
        Find available input/output devices, then wait for incoming calls..
        1. List the available playback and recording devices.
        2. Set the current devices (input, output, notification) to the first device in their respective list.
        3. Initialize the speaker volume level.
        4. Wait for in-coming calls.
        Parameters:
        mySession - Populated session object
        Since:
        1.0

      • doMakeCall

        public com.skype.api.Participant doMakeCall(String myCallTarget,
                                   boolean videoCall)
        Start calling myCallTarget
        1. setupAudioDevices(0, 0)
        2. initiate conversation
        3. locate participant matching myCallTarget
        4. invoke call on myCallTarget
        5. return Participant myCallTarget
        Parameters:
        myCallTarget - The skype-name of the person you would like to call
        videoCall - Boolean deciding whether to enable video
        Returns:
        Participant If no audio and/or video (if videoCall is true) is found this method will return null
